quran[23]{c,v,t}:
  51,52,"Likewise, no messenger came to those before them without being told: “A magician, or a madman!”"
  51,53,"Did they suggest this to one another? Rather they are transgressing people."
  51,54,"So turn away from them [O Prophet], for you are not to blame."
  51,55,"But keep reminding them, for reminder benefits the believers."
  51,56,"I have not created the jinn and mankind except to worship Me."
  51,57,"I seek no provision from them, nor do I want them to feed Me."
  51,58,"Indeed, it is Allah Who is the All-Provider, Lord of Power, the Mighty."
  51,59,"Indeed, those who do wrong will have a share [of punishment] like that of their predecessors, so let them not ask Me to hasten it."
  51,60,"So woe to those who disbelieve from [the punishment of] the Day which they are promised."
  52,1,"By the mount of Tūr,"
  52,2,"and by the Book inscribed"
  52,3,"on an unrolled parchment,"
  52,4,"and by the much-frequented House,"
  52,5,"and by the canopy raised high,"
  52,6,"and by the sea set on fire."
  52,7,"The punishment of your Lord will surely come to pass;"
  52,8,"there is none who can avert it."
  52,9,"On the Day when the heaven will convulse violently,"
  52,10,"and the mountains will move a horrible movement."
  52,11,"Then woe to the deniers on that Day,"
  52,12,"those who amuse themselves in falsehood."
  52,13,"On the Day when they will be shoved into the Fire forcefully,"
  52,14,"[They will be told,] “This is the Fire which you used to deny."